#wellnesswednesday There is this idea that everyone who eats smoothie bowls is vibrant and happy all the time! Social media can portray these types of images which I think can send a dangerous message. .
.
I had someone once make a comment how "I should never be tired because I always drink green smoothies", followed by a wink 😉. Like the suggestion that my eating habits must not be working cause I expressed I was tired that day. .
.
Regardless of what you eat, you can have days where you feel tired, sick, or bummed out. . 🥗Good nutrition gives our body the raw materials it needs to keep immune function up and our body more tools to work with. However, stress, shifts in hormones, seasonal weather changes, or a fight with your loved one that morning all creates a stress response in the body that then impacts our immune system, energy, and mood. 
So it's ok to not be ok all time, we are all human and have better days than others. 
On your low days listen to your body and give it what it needs. This could be a relaxing bath, hitting the gym, or a enjoying a piece of dark chocolate 🍫. Accept its ok not to be ok all the time, listen to what your body needs, and support yourself to feel better in the way that makes the most sense to you ❤️
.
.

Sanskrit tapasyā, literally "produced by heat", refers to a personal endeavor of discipline, undertaken to achieve a goal. 
In Kundalini yoga that discipline is a 40-day sadhana practice of yoga and #meditation.

This #workshop will #inspire you to begin a 40 day practice or renew your sadhana by delving deep into the answers to these 4 questions:  Why do I need this #discipline ?  How can I achieve my #goals ?  When is the best #time for me to #practice ? Where is the best location for my #sadhana 
Join Kathe Forrest (Sirikirin) – author of The 40 Day Sadhana Companion, as we #examine these #questions #together and #understand the #science behind this #amazing #yoga .

It took my a while to #understand these things but as I look at who I've very very very selectively surrounded myself with I'm #grateful to God for the ways He has grown my #wisdom and #discernment concerning who should be in my inner circle and who should be in the outer courts or not even in the camp. Hey hi hello everyone! Yes i'm still here! 
Sorry for disappearing for a while.. i'v been facing some hard challenges lately that have managed to drive my strength and positivity down hill.. usually i'm able to keep strong and stay positive but it got to the point of not being able to do something about these obstacles (i hit a brick wall basically). I have not felt helpful whatsoever. I'v felt completely useless and hated seeing the ones i love upset. Life can definitely feel like it is against you, making you feel like everyone/everything is out to get you. I still don't understand why it happens to the people who have always been good to others and have worked hard their whole life; gone through some terrible shit yet still they're the ones who cop the worst through life... no, it doesn't seem fair.  But that's how it is. It does not matter if your a good person or a bad person, it can happen to anyone. Instead of feeling sorry for myself any more than i already have; it is time to face reality. This quote says it all. .
